  "finger_focus": "Right pinky / and \\, Shift+minus for _",
  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Two new marks, both quiet workhorses. The backslash leans the other way from the slash you already know - it walks a Windows path and opens an escape. The underscore joins words where a space cannot, in a filename or a variable. Small marks, but they keep technical writing tidy."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "The backslash sits at the top right, above Enter, just past the square brackets; strike it with the right pinky, no Shift. The underscore shares the minus key: hold Shift and press the minus, again with the right pinky. So minus is plain, underscore is Shift."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "keyboard",
      "title": "Which way does it lean",
      "text": "The forward slash leans right and splits a path; the backslash leans left and escapes a character. Keep the two straight in your head and your fingers will not mix them up."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "\\ \\ \\ a\\b c\\d \\n \\t \\ \\",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "The backslash",
      "hint": "Right pinky, top right, no Shift. It leans the opposite way from /."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "_ _ _ my_file _temp_ a_b _ _",
      "finger": "orange",
      "title": "The underscore",
      "hint": "Shift plus minus, right pinky. It joins words with no space."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "src/main.js /home/user my_file.txt C:\\Users",
      "finger": "green",
      "title": "Paths and names",
      "hint": "Forward slashes for the path, a backslash for Windows, underscore in the name."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "These earn their place in paths, filenames, and code. The forward slash for a route, the backslash for an escape, the underscore where a name needs no gap. Set them down with care and the next reader follows the path without a stumble."
    }
  ],
  "character_tips": {
